{"id":839,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":839,"title":"Megiddo","subtitle":"","short_title":"Megiddo","uri":"/scriptures/bd/megiddo","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/megiddo.t1","order":".000.2196"},[".title","Megiddo"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/megiddo.p1","order":".000.2197"},"On the southwestern side of the plain of Esdraelon, and on the caravan route from Egypt to Damascus. Frequently mentioned in Israelite history. The scene of Sisera’s defeat (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/judg/5.19"},"Judg. 5:19"],"). Fortified by Solomon (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-kgs/9.15"},"1 Kgs. 9:15"],"). The place where Ahaziah died of his wounds (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/9.27"},"2 Kgs. 9:27"],"). Also the scene of the tragic defeat and death of King Josiah (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-kgs/23.29-30"},"23:29–30"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/2-chr/35.22"},"2 Chr. 35:22"],"). In",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/zech/12.11"},"Zech. 12:11"],"the place is called “the valley of Megiddon.” See also",["i",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bd/armageddon"},"Armageddon"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bd/esdraelon"},"Esdraelon"],"."]]]],"refs":null}
